<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Wyld</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-18 23:33:26</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well those of you who think this weapon sucks simply are too small minded to know how to use it correctly.<BR>
My Troll SK weilds this as an OPENER to battle. I often get double attacks of more than 100 damage. That's 200 or more damage that I would never have gotten using my regular dark reaver(or mith 2hndr)<BR>
As soon as it swings, swap it out with your regular weapon. You guys who complain about the delay sure aren't thinking of this weapon's potential!<BR>
<BR>
Swing with the weighted axe and then equip a regular weapon as fast as possible. <BR>
Unless your swing is bad (misses/gets parried/blocked/etc), you will always do more damage then by using your regular weapon alone.<BR>
<BR>
For those of you (excluding Warriors with riposte discipline in mind) that are equipping this axe and actually using it through an entire battle, it's not the weighted axe that sucks, it's you! =)</font></td></tr></table>
